sm.Tulchinsky employs historical sources not used before to explain how Salsberg’s family life and surrounding religious and social milieu influenced his evolution as a Zionist, an important labour union leader, a member of the Communist Party of Canada, and a prominent member of Toronto’s Jewish community.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCommunistszOntariovBiography. 0aJewszOntariozTorontovBiography. 0aLabor union memberszOntariovBiography. 0aPoliticianszOntariovBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266531640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442665316423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442665316.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK